# Composable Components Pattern

## Rule

**ALWAYS prefer composable (compound) components over monolithic components with many props.** When a component has 3+ configuration props or needs flexible layouts, use the compound component pattern.

## Pattern

```tsx
// ❌ BAD: Monolithic with prop drilling
interface NavbarProps {
  onOpenSidebar: () => void;
  onNewChat: () => void;
  showNewChat?: boolean;
  showTitle?: boolean;
  title?: string;
  rightActions?: ReactNode;
}

function Navbar({ onOpenSidebar, onNewChat, showNewChat, showTitle, title, rightActions }: NavbarProps) {
  return (
    <div className="flex items-center justify-between">
      <HamburgerButton onClick={onOpenSidebar} />
      {showTitle && <h1>{title}</h1>}
      {rightActions}
      {showNewChat && <NewChatButton onClick={onNewChat} />}
    </div>
  );
}

// ✅ GOOD: Composable compound component
export const Navbar = {
  Root: ({ children, className }: { children: ReactNode; className?: string }) => (
    <div className={cn('flex items-center justify-between', className)}>{children}</div>
  ),
  Hamburger: ({ onClick }: { onClick: () => void }) => (
    <HamburgerButton onClick={onClick} />
  ),
  Title: ({ children }: { children: ReactNode }) => (
    <h1 className="flex-1 truncate">{children}</h1>
  ),
  Actions: ({ children }: { children: ReactNode }) => (
    <div className="flex items-center gap-2">{children}</div>
  ),
  NewChat: ({ onClick }: { onClick: () => void }) => (
    <NewChatButton onClick={onClick} />
  ),
};
```

## Usage

```tsx
// Minimal
<Navbar.Root>
  <Navbar.Hamburger onClick={openSidebar} />
  <Navbar.NewChat onClick={onNewChat} />
</Navbar.Root>

// With title
<Navbar.Root>
  <Navbar.Hamburger onClick={openSidebar} />
  <Navbar.Title>Page Title</Navbar.Title>
  <Navbar.NewChat onClick={onNewChat} />
</Navbar.Root>

// Custom layout - no prop changes needed
<Navbar.Root>
  <Navbar.Hamburger onClick={openSidebar} />
  <Navbar.Actions>
    <ShareButton />
    <Navbar.NewChat onClick={onNewChat} />
  </Navbar.Actions>
</Navbar.Root>
```

## When to Use

| Composable Pattern | Monolithic Props |
|--------------------|------------------|
| 3+ layout variations | Single fixed layout |
| Flexible child ordering | Strict child order |
| Custom elements between parts | No custom injection |
| Reusable across pages | Single-use component |

## Benefits

- **No prop explosion**: Add features without new props
- **Flexible layouts**: Consumers control structure
- **Type-safe slots**: Each part has its own interface
- **Storybook-friendly**: Easy to showcase variations
